# Feature 2: View Stored Predefined Prompts

//Done
## User Story 2.1: View list of stored prompts
As a user,
I want to view all the predefined prompts I previously stored,
So that I can quickly reuse them without retyping.

//DONE
### Acceptance Criteria 2.1.1: Display prompt list on request
Given the user has previously stored at least one predefined prompt
AND the user is logged into the Pen application
When the user navigates to the "Prompts" section
Then the system displays a scrollable list of all stored prompts
AND orders the prompts by their creation date, with the most recent last.

//Dome
### Acceptance Criteria 2.1.2: Empty state handling
Given the user has not stored any predefined prompts
AND the user is logged into the Pen application
When the user navigates to the "Prompts" section
Then the system displays an empty state view
And the empty state contains:
    - An illustration icon
    - Text: "No prompts saved yet"


//Done
# Feature 3: Manage Predefined Prompts (Delete, Edit, Create)

## User Story 3.1: Delete a prompt
As a user,
I want to delete a predefined prompt,
So that I can remove any prompt I no longer need.

### Acceptance Criteria 3.1.1: Delete prompt action
Given the user is viewing the list of stored predefined prompts
When the user clicks on the "Delete" button next to a prompt
Then the system displays a confirmation dialog
    
### Acceptance Criteria 3.1.2: Confirm deletion
Given the user is on the confirmation dialog
When the user confirms the deletion
Then the selected prompt is removed from the list
And deleted from the database
    
### Acceptance Criteria 3.1.3: Cancel deletion
Given the user is on the confirmation dialog
When the user cancels the deletion
Then the prompt is not deleted
And the list remains unchanged

---
//Done
## User Story 3.2: Edit a prompt
As a user,
I want to edit a predefined prompt,
So that I can update its content if needed.

### Acceptance Criteria 3.2.1: Edit prompt action
Given the user is viewing the list of stored predefined prompts
When the user clicks on the "Edit" button next to a prompt
Then the system opens a modal or new screen with the prompt's full content editable.

### Acceptance Criteria 3.2.2: Save edited prompt
Given the user has edited the prompt content
When the user clicks "Save"
Then the system saves the updated prompt
And the prompt in the list reflects the new content
AND displays a pop up message to inform the user the prompt is updated successfully.


### Acceptance Criteria 3.2.3: Cancel edit
Given the user is editing a prompt
When the user clicks "Cancel"
Then the system discards the changes
And the user is returned to the prompt list view
AND displays a pop up message to inform the user the edit is cancelled and changes are discarded.

---

## User Story 3.3: Create a new prompt
As a user,
I want to create a new predefined prompt,
So that I can store new prompts for future use.

### Acceptance Criteria 3.3.1: Open create prompt screen
Given the user is in the "Prompts" section
When the user clicks on the "New" button
Then the system opens a screen or modal where the user can enter:
    - Prompt title (text input)
    - Prompt content (text input, multiline)
    - supports markdown formatting

### Acceptance Criteria 3.3.2: Save new prompt
Given the user has entered both title and content for the new prompt
When the user clicks "Save"
Then the system saves the new prompt
And the prompt is displayed in the prompt list
AND displays a pop up message to inform the user the prompt is saved successfully.

### Acceptance Criteria 3.3.3: Validation for empty fields
Given the user is trying to create a new prompt
When the user leaves either the title or content field empty
AND the user clicks "Save"
Then display a pop up message to inform the user that both title and content are required.
